cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on the detection of adversarial examples in deep neural networks, which is a common problem in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses various attack and defense techniques, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
